The <b>Short-crested Coquette</b>, <b>Coquette Du Guerrero</b>, <b>Coqueta Cresticorta</b>, or <b>Coqueta De Guerrero</b> (<i>Lophornis brachylophus</i>) is a species of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hummingbird" title="Hummingbird">hummingbird</a> in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trochilidae" title="Trochilidae" class="mw-redirect">Trochilidae</a> family. It is found only in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico" title="Mexico">Mexico</a>. Its natural <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habitat" title="Habitat">habitats</a> are subtropical or tropical moist <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Montane_forest" title="Montane forest" class="mw-redirect">montane forests</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plantation" title="Plantation">plantations</a> . It is threatened by <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habitat_loss" title="Habitat loss" class="mw-redirect">habitat loss</a>.
